@Node "Introduction" "GMS_mailer.guide/Introduction"
@Next "Installation"
@Toc  "Main"

   @{b}Introduction@{ub}


   This  document describes, in short, but hopefully thorough, terms how to
use the different functions in GMS mailer.

   @{b}Please  read it carefully !@{ub}  Many of the problems a user can have in the
use of a program, can be solved by carefully reading the manual.


  @{" Overall Information " link "Overall"}   What is GMS mailer
  @{" Bonds               " link "Bounds"}   Requirements of GMS mailer
  @{" Installation        " link "Installation"}   Installation information
  @{" Running GMS Maier   " link "Starting GMS mailer"}   How to start GMS mailer
  @{" Features            " link "Features"}   The specifications

@EndNode

@Node "Overall" "GMS_mailer.guide/Overall"
@Next "Bonds"
@Toc  "Introduction"

   @{b}Overall Information@{ub}


GMS mailer is a Full FTN Mailer for Nodes and Points for Amiga Computers.


GMS  Mailer  uses  the  Magic User Interface  (@{"MUI" link "MUI"}) by Stefan Stuntz, this
gives to GMS mailer a unique Graphical User Interface.
@EndNode

@Node "Bounds" "GMS_mailer.guide/Bounds"
@Next "Installation"
@Prev "Overall"
@Toc  "Introduction"

   @{b}Bonds@{ub}


GMS mailer has only a few requirements in order to work properly:

  - AmigaOS 2.04 or higher (localisation available from AmigaOS 2.1).
  - MUI 2.1 or higher.
@EndNode

@Node "Installation" "GMS_mailer.guide/Installation"
@Next "Mailer basics"
@Prev "Introduction"
@Toc  "Introduction"

   @{b}Installation of GMS mailer@{ub}


   Please  use  the  appropriate installation icon in the `Install' drawer.
It  uses  Commodore's  Installer utility and will copy all the files in the
appropriate directories, it will also add some assigns to your User-Startup
and  will ask you some information so as to create a default configuration.
After that you will be able to immediatelly run GMS mailer.


   GMS  mailer  is  distributed  with  several  (sub)directories,  with  a
`GMS:' assign necessary to function as the "root" directory:

        GMS:
         |
         + Bin                  --> GMS_mailer
         |
         + Docs                 --> Documentations
         |
         + Config               --> Mailer[.x]/MailerSettings ...
         |
         + Externals            --> Some required file...
         |
         + Install              --> Install-script(s)
         |
         + Libs                 --> GMS.library GMS_mailer.library ...
         |
         + Locale               --> Language/Locale files
         |
         + Rexx                 --> GMS_CallNode.rexx ...


   If  you are a Registered User, you must put the `GMS_mailer.key' file in
the `GMS:' directory, for the program to properly recognize it.
@EndNode

@Node "Starting GMS mailer" "GMS_mailer.guide/Starting GMS mailer"
@Next "GUI"
@Prev "Configuration"
@Toc  "Introduction"

   @{b}Running GMS mailer@{ub}


   You can run GMS mailer from the Workbench, Shell or from @{b}ARexx@{ub}.
The command line syntax for GMS mailer is:

   GMS_mailer [LINE/N] [CONFIG/M] [NONEW/S] [NOLOCK/S]


@{b}CONFIG/M@{ub}

Modify MailerSettings configuration keywords. Many can be specified.


@{b}LINE/N@{ub}

Specify  the  line number of the mailer.  This means the configuration will
be  fetched  from the drawer named GMS:Config/Mailer.x, where x is the line
number.

If you don't specify a line number, GMS mailer uses the line 0 as default.

It  is  also  used  for  default  settings.  IE settings in that drawer are
global.  The can be overidden by individual line settings but if they don't
specify a setting, they will be fetched from this line 0 drawer.


@{b}NONEW/S@{ub}

If the mailer is not running, it doesn't start a new mailer process.


@{b}NOLOCK/S@{ub}

If the mailer is already running, it doesn't create another User-Interface.


@{b}Error codes@{ub}

GMS  mailer when spawed in answer mode OFF it set up these error codes when
it exits:

0  - All ok
5  - Out of memory
10 - Session failure



Examples:  GMS_mailer Line 1
           GMS_mailer CallNode=2:331/106@fidonet.org
           GMS_mailer Line 1 Answer=on

@EndNode

@Node "Features" "GMS_mailer.guide/Features"
@Prev "Starting GMS mailer"
@Toc  "Introduction"

   @{b}Features of GMS mailer@{ub}


  GMS mailer...

   ... is Faaaaaaaast. Uses little cpu time...
   ... is fully localized (Workbench 2.1 or higher).
   ... is able to deal with full 5 dimensional addressing.
   ... is able to manage Fax and Voice calls.
   ... has a powerful ARexx interface.
   ... supports Nodelists.
   ... supports the OwnDevUnit.library.
   ... supports FTS-1, YooHoo, Emsi and @{b}Emsi-II@{ub} handshakes.
   ... supports unidirectional protocols like DietIfna, ZedZip, ZedZap, DirectZap.
   ... supports bi-directional protocols like @{b}Hydra@{ub}.
   ... is a @{b}MUI@{ub} Application !!
   ... works also without MUI !!
   ... has many many other features !
@EndNode

