@Node "MS ExtCmds AfterSession" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/AfterSession"
@Next "MS ExtCmds AfterSessionFailed"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      AfterSession=<command>

   This is used to set the command line that GMS mailer will execute at the
end of a session.

   There may be embedded %-commands:

   %a      aka of the remote system (one aka per %a)
   %A      all akas of the remote system (space separated)
   %b      baudrate (between computer and modem)
   %B      baudrate (of the actual connection)
   %C      full CONNECT message from the modem
   %s      serial device name
   %u      serial device unit number
   %f      serial device flags
   %r      unique random number (timestamp)
   %l      name of logfile
   %L      name of log callerID
   %Z      zone number of the other system     
   %N      net number of the other system
   %F      fido node number of the other system
   %P      point number of the other system
   %D      domain name of the other system (if available)
   %n      complete address of the other system
   %I      name of <GlobalInbound>
   %O      name of <GlobalOutbound>
   %S      name of Sysop of other system
   %d      direction: 1 if inbound call, -1 if outbound call
   %x      this TrxID string
   %X      remote TrxID string
   %m      line number of this system


Example:   AfterSession="rx rexx:MM_import.rexx"


See also:     @{"AlwaysAfterSession" Link "MS ExtCmds AlwaysAfterSession"}

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds AfterSessionFailed" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/AfterSessionFailed"
@Next "MS ExtCmds AfterSessionPri"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds AfterSession"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      AfterSessionFailed=<boolean>

   Spawn the <AfterSession> command also if the session is failed.


Example:   AfterSessionFailed=OFF

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds AfterSessionPri" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/AfterSessionPri"
@Next "MS ExtCmds AfterSessionStack"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds AfterSessionFailed"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      AfterSessionPri=<pri>

   Set the priority of the <AfterSession> command.


Example:   AfterSessionPri=1

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds AfterSessionStack" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/AfterSessionStack"
@Next "MS ExtCmds AlwaysAfterSession"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds AfterSessionPri"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      AfterSessionStack=<stack>

   Set the stack size for <AfterSession> command.


Example:   AfterSessionStack=5000

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds AlwaysAfterSession" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/AlwaysAfterSession"
@Next "MS ExtCmds BeforeSession"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds AfterSessionStack"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      AlwaysAfterSession=<boolean>

   With  this  keyword  you can decide to spawn the AfterSession command at
the end of all sessions or only at the end of a FidoNet session.


Example:   AlwaysAfterSession=ON

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds BeforeSession" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/BeforeSession"
@Next "MS ExtCmds BeforeSessionPri"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds AlwaysAfterSession"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      BeforeSession=<command>

   This  is used to set the command line that GMS mailer will execute after
the CONNECT string.

   There may be embedded %-commands:

   %a      aka of the remote system (one aka per %a)
   %A      all akas of the remote system (space separated)
   %b      baudrate (between computer and modem)
   %B      baudrate (of the actual connection)
   %C      full CONNECT message from the modem
   %s      serial device name
   %u      serial device unit number
   %f      serial device flags
   %r      unique random number (timestamp)
   %l      name of logfile
   %L      name of log callerID
   %Z      zone number of the other system     
   %N      net number of the other system
   %F      fido node number of the other system
   %P      point number of the other system
   %D      domain name of the other system (if available)
   %n      complete address of the other system
   %I      name of <GlobalInbound>
   %O      name of <GlobalOutbound>
   %S      name of Sysop of other system
   %d      direction: 1 if inbound call, -1 if outbound call
   %x      this TrxID string
   %X      remote TrxID string
   %m      line number of this system


Example:   BeforeSession="rx play Door-Bell.iff"

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds BeforeSessionPri" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/BeforeSessionPri"
@Next "MS ExtCmds BeforeSessionStack"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds BeforeSession"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      BeforeSessionPri=<pri>

   Set the priority of the <BeforeSession> command.


Example:   BeforeSessionPri=2

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds BeforeSessionStack" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/BeforeSessionStack"
@Next "MS ExtCmds Dialer"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds BeforeSessionPri"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      BeforeSessionStack=<stack>

   Set the stack size for <BeforeSession> command.


Example:   BeforeSessionStack=5000

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds Dialer" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Handshakes/External commands/Dialer"
@Next "MS ExtCmds DialerPri"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds BeforeSessionStack"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      Dialer=<command>

   Use this if you have a custom dial-out program.

   There may be embedded %-commands:

   %a      aka of the remote system (one aka per %a)
   %A      all akas of the remote system (space separated)
   %b      baudrate (between computer and modem)
   %B      baudrate (of the actual connection)
   %C      full CONNECT message from the modem
   %s      serial device name
   %u      serial device unit number
   %f      serial device flags
   %r      unique random number (timestamp)
   %l      name of logfile
   %L      name of log callerID
   %Z      zone number of the other system     
   %N      net number of the other system
   %F      fido node number of the other system
   %P      point number of the other system
   %D      domain name of the other system (if available)
   %n      complete address of the other system
   %I      name of <GlobalInbound>
   %O      name of <GlobalOutbound>
   %S      name of Sysop of other system
   %d      direction: 1 if inbound call, -1 if outbound call
   %x      this TrxID string
   %X      remote TrxID string
   %m      line number of this system


Example:   Dialer=CallPCP

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds DialerPri" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/DialerPri"
@Next "MS ExtCmds DialerStack"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds Dialer"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      DialerPri=<pri>

   Set the priority of the <Dialer> command.


Example:   DialerPri=0

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds DialerStack" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/DialerStack"
@Next "MS ExtCmds EndSession"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds DialerPri"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      DialerStack=<stack>

   Set the stack size for <Dialer> command.


Example:   DialerStack=4000

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds EndSession" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/EndSession"
@Next "MS ExtCmds EndSessionPri"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds DialerStack"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      EndSession=<command>

   GMS mailer will spawn this command only at the end of a FidoNet session.

   There may be embedded %-commands:

   %a      aka of the remote system (one aka per %a)
   %A      all akas of the remote system (space separated)
   %b      baudrate (between computer and modem)
   %B      baudrate (of the actual connection)
   %C      full CONNECT message from the modem
   %s      serial device name
   %u      serial device unit number
   %f      serial device flags
   %r      unique random number (timestamp)
   %l      name of logfile
   %L      name of log callerID
   %Z      zone number of the other system     
   %N      net number of the other system
   %F      fido node number of the other system
   %P      point number of the other system
   %D      domain name of the other system (if available)
   %n      complete address of the other system
   %I      name of <GlobalInbound>
   %O      name of <GlobalOutbound>
   %S      name of Sysop of other system
   %d      direction: 1 if inbound call, -1 if outbound call
   %x      this TrxID string
   %X      remote TrxID string
   %m      line number of this system


Example:   EndSession=""

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds EndSessionPri" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/EndSessionPri"
@Next "MS ExtCmds EndSessionStack"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds EndSession"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      EndSessionPri=<pri>

   Set the priority of the <EndSession> command.


Example:   EndSessionPri=1

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds EndSessionStack" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/EndSessionStack"
@Next "MS ExtCmds FileRequest"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds EndSessionPri"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      EndSessionStack=<stack>

   Set the stack size for <EndSession> command.


Example:   EndSessionStack=4000

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds FileRequest" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/FileRequest"
@Next "MS ExtCmds FileRequestPri"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds EndSessionStack"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      FileRequest=<command>

   This  is  the command that GMS mailer will spawn when it receives a file
request. It should obviously launch a freq handler if you support that
capability.

   There may be embedded %-commands:

   %a      aka of the remote system (one aka per %a)
   %A      all akas of the remote system (space separated)
   %b      baudrate (between computer and modem)
   %B      baudrate (of the actual connection)
   %C      full CONNECT message from the modem
   %s      serial device name
   %u      serial device unit number
   %f      serial device flags
   %r      unique random number (timestamp)
   %l      name of logfile
   %L      name of log callerID
   %Z      zone number of the other system     
   %N      net number of the other system
   %F      fido node number of the other system
   %P      point number of the other system
   %D      domain name of the other system (if available)
   %n      complete address of the other system
   %I      name of <GlobalInbound>
   %O      name of <GlobalOutbound>
   %S      name of Sysop of other system
   %d      direction: 1 if inbound call, -1 if outbound call
   %x      this TrxID string
   %X      remote TrxID string
   %m      line number of this system

   %i      specify the name of #?.REQ file
   %o      specify the name of output #?.RLO file


Example:   FileRequest="rx frequest %i,%o,%l"
           FileRequest="ZFTell SERVE \\"i=%i o=%o s=%B a=%n n=%S\\""

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds FileRequestPri" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/FileRequestPri"
@Next "MS ExtCmds FileRequestStack"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds FileRequest"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      FileRequestPri=<pri>

   Set the priority of the <FileRequest> command.


Example:   FileRequestPri=0

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds FileRequestStack" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/FileRequestStack"
@Next "MS ExtCmds FileRequestNone"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds FileRequestPri"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      FileRequestStack=<stack>

   Set the stack size for <FileRequest> command.


Example:   FileRequestStack=10000

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds FileRequestNone" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/FileRequestNone"
@Next "MS ExtCmds FileRequestNonePri"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds FileRequestStack"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      FileRequestNone=<command>

   This  is  the command that GMS mailer will spawn when it receives a file
request  and  BBSmode  is  set  to None.  It should obviously launch a freq
handler if you support that capability.

   There may be embedded %-commands:

   %a      aka of the remote system (one aka per %a)
   %A      all akas of the remote system (space separated)
   %b      baudrate (between computer and modem)
   %B      baudrate (of the actual connection)
   %C      full CONNECT message from the modem
   %s      serial device name
   %u      serial device unit number
   %f      serial device flags
   %r      unique random number (timestamp)
   %l      name of logfile
   %L      name of log callerID
   %Z      zone number of the other system     
   %N      net number of the other system
   %F      fido node number of the other system
   %P      point number of the other system
   %D      domain name of the other system (if available)
   %n      complete address of the other system
   %I      name of <GlobalInbound>
   %O      name of <GlobalOutbound>
   %S      name of Sysop of other system
   %d      direction: 1 if inbound call, -1 if outbound call
   %x      this TrxID string
   %X      remote TrxID string
   %m      line number of this system

   %i      specify the name of #?.REQ file
   %o      specify the name of output #?.RLO file


Example:   FileRequestNone="rx frequest %i,%o,%l"
           FileRequestNone="ZFTell SERVE \\"i=%i o=%o s=%B a=%n n=%S\\""

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds FileRequestNonePri" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/FileRequestNonePri"
@Next "MS ExtCmds FileRequestNoneStack"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds FileRequestNone"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      FileRequestNonePri=<pri>

   Set the priority of the <FileRequestNone> command.


Example:   FileRequestNonePri=0

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds FileRequestNoneStack" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/FileRequestNoneStack"
@Next "MS ExtCmds FileRequestZMH"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds FileRequestNonePri"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      FileRequestNoneStack=<stack>

   Set the stack size for <FileRequestNone> command.


Example:   FileRequestNoneStack=10000

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds FileRequestZMH" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/FileRequestZMH"
@Next "MS ExtCmds FileRequestZMHPri"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds FileRequestNoneStack"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      FileRequestZMH=<command>

   This  is  the command that GMS mailer will spawn when it receives a file
request  in  ZMH  mode.   It  should obviously launch a freq handler if you
support that capability.

   There may be embedded %-commands:

   %a      aka of the remote system (one aka per %a)
   %A      all akas of the remote system (space separated)
   %b      baudrate (between computer and modem)
   %B      baudrate (of the actual connection)
   %C      full CONNECT message from the modem
   %s      serial device name
   %u      serial device unit number
   %f      serial device flags
   %r      unique random number (timestamp)
   %l      name of logfile
   %L      name of log callerID
   %Z      zone number of the other system     
   %N      net number of the other system
   %F      fido node number of the other system
   %P      point number of the other system
   %D      domain name of the other system (if available)
   %n      complete address of the other system
   %I      name of <GlobalInbound>
   %O      name of <GlobalOutbound>
   %S      name of Sysop of other system
   %d      direction: 1 if inbound call, -1 if outbound call
   %x      this TrxID string
   %X      remote TrxID string
   %m      line number of this system

   %i      specify the name of #?.REQ file
   %o      specify the name of output #?.RLO file


Example:   FileRequestZMH="rx frequest %i,%o,%l"
           FileRequestZMH="ZFTell SERVE \\"i=%i o=%o s=%B a=%n n=%S\\""

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds FileRequestZMHPri" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/FileRequestZMHPri"
@Next "MS ExtCmds FileRequestZMHStack"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds FileRequestZMH"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      FileRequestZMHPri=<pri>

   Set the priority of the <FileRequestZMH> command.


Example:   FileRequestZMHPri=1

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds FileRequestZMHStack" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/FileRequestZMHStack"
@Next "MS ExtCmds RingCommand"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds FileRequestZMHPri"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      FileRequestZMHStack=<stack>

   Set the stack size for <FileRequestZMH> command.


Example:   FileRequestZMHStack=10000

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds RingCommand" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/RingCommand"
@Next "MS ExtCmds RingPri"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds FileRequestZMHStack"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      RingCommand=<command>

   Set the command to be executed when a `RING' is received from the modem.

   There may be embedded %-commands:

   %a      aka of the remote system (one aka per %a)
   %A      all akas of the remote system (space separated)
   %b      baudrate (between computer and modem)
   %B      baudrate (of the actual connection)
   %C      full CONNECT message from the modem
   %s      serial device name
   %u      serial device unit number
   %f      serial device flags
   %r      unique random number (timestamp)
   %l      name of logfile
   %L      name of log callerID
   %Z      zone number of the other system     
   %N      net number of the other system
   %F      fido node number of the other system
   %P      point number of the other system
   %D      domain name of the other system (if available)
   %n      complete address of the other system
   %I      name of <GlobalInbound>
   %O      name of <GlobalOutbound>
   %S      name of Sysop of other system
   %d      direction: 1 if inbound call, -1 if outbound call
   %x      this TrxID string
   %X      remote TrxID string
   %m      line number of this system


Example:   RingCommand="rx play Beep"

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds RingPri" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/RingPri"
@Next "MS ExtCmds RingStack"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds RingCommand"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      RingPri=<pri>

   Set the priority of the <RingCommand> command.


Example:   RingPri=0

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds RingStack" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/RingStack"
@Next "MS ExtCmds StartSession"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds RingPri"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      RingStack=<stack>

   Set the stack size for <RingCommand> command.


Example:   RingStack=4000

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds StartSession" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/StartSession"
@Next "MS ExtCmds StartSessionPri"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds RingStack"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      StartSession=<command>

   GMS  mailer  will  spawn this command at the beginning of a FidoNet file
transfer session, after the handshake.

   There may be embedded %-commands:

   %a      aka of the remote system (one aka per %a)
   %A      all akas of the remote system (space separated)
   %b      baudrate (between computer and modem)
   %B      baudrate (of the actual connection)
   %C      full CONNECT message from the modem
   %s      serial device name
   %u      serial device unit number
   %f      serial device flags
   %r      unique random number (timestamp)
   %l      name of logfile
   %L      name of log callerID
   %Z      zone number of the other system     
   %N      net number of the other system
   %F      fido node number of the other system
   %P      point number of the other system
   %D      domain name of the other system (if available)
   %n      complete address of the other system
   %I      name of <GlobalInbound>
   %O      name of <GlobalOutbound>
   %S      name of Sysop of other system
   %d      direction: 1 if inbound call, -1 if outbound call
   %x      this TrxID string
   %X      remote TrxID string
   %m      line number of this system


Example:   StartSession=""

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds StartSessionPri" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/StartSessionPri"
@Next "MS ExtCmds StartSessionStack"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds StartSession"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      StartSessionPri=<pri>

   Set the priority of the <StartSession> command.


Example:   StartSessionPri=-1

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds StartSessionStack" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/StartSessionStack"
@Next "MS ExtCmds TurnSide"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds StartSessionPri"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      StartSessionStack=<stack>

   Set the stack size for <StartSession> command.


Example:   StartSessionStack=4000

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds TurnSide" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/TurnSide"
@Next "MS ExtCmds TurnSidePri"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds RingStack"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      TurnSide=<command>

   GMS  mailer  will  execute  the  given  command  line  when  the session
"turnaround" is about to take place.  Session turnaround is when the sender
and  the  receiver  change  sides,  and  files are transferred in the other
direction  afterwards.   Since GMS mailer waits for the external command to
complete before continuing with the session, it should return quickly.

   There may be embedded %-commands:

   %a      aka of the remote system (one aka per %a)
   %A      all akas of the remote system (space separated)
   %b      baudrate (between computer and modem)
   %B      baudrate (of the actual connection)
   %C      full CONNECT message from the modem
   %s      serial device name
   %u      serial device unit number
   %f      serial device flags
   %r      unique random number (timestamp)
   %l      name of logfile
   %L      name of log callerID
   %Z      zone number of the other system     
   %N      net number of the other system
   %F      fido node number of the other system
   %P      point number of the other system
   %D      domain name of the other system (if available)
   %n      complete address of the other system
   %I      name of <GlobalInbound>
   %O      name of <GlobalOutbound>
   %S      name of Sysop of other system
   %d      direction: 1 if inbound call, -1 if outbound call
   %x      this TrxID string
   %X      remote TrxID string
   %m      line number of this system


Example:   TurnSide="rexx rx:Import.ems"

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds TurnSidePri" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/TurnSidePri"
@Next "MS ExtCmds TurnSideStack"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds TurnSide"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      TurnSidePri=<pri>

   Set the priority of the <TurnSide> command.


Example:   TurnSidePri=2

@EndNode

@Node "MS ExtCmds TurnSideStack" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/External commands/TurnSideStack"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds TurnSidePri"
@Toc  "MS ExtCmds"

Name:      TurnSideStack=<stack>

   Set the stack size for <TurnSide> command.


Example:   TurnSideStack=12000

@EndNode

@Node "MS Fax" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Fax"
@Next "MS Hs"
@Prev "MS ExtCmds"
@Toc  "CFG MailerSettings"

   @{b}Fax options@{ub}


   With these keywords you can configure a complete Fax session.

 @{" FaxInCommand  " Link "MS Fax FaxInCommand"}
 @{" FaxInPri      " Link "MS Fax FaxInPri"}
 @{" FaxInStack    " Link "MS Fax FaxInStack"}
 @{" FaxOutCommand " Link "MS Fax FaxOutCommand"}
 @{" FaxOutPri     " Link "MS Fax FaxOutPri"}
 @{" FaxOutStack   " Link "MS Fax FaxOutStack"}
 @{" FaxString     " Link "MS Fax FaxString"}

@EndNode

@Node "MS Fax FaxInCommand" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Fax/FaxInCommand"
@Next "MS Fax FaxInPri"
@Toc  "MS Fax"

Name:      FaxInCommand=<comando>

   In  Answer  mode  ON,  when GMS mailer detects a fax connection, it will
spawn this external program.

   There may be embedded %-commands:

   %a      aka of the remote system (one aka per %a)
   %A      all akas of the remote system (space separated)
   %b      baudrate (between computer and modem)
   %B      baudrate (of the actual connection)
   %C      full CONNECT message from the modem
   %s      serial device name
   %u      serial device unit number
   %f      serial device flags
   %r      unique random number (timestamp)
   %l      name of logfile
   %L      name of log callerID
   %Z      zone number of the other system     
   %N      net number of the other system
   %F      fido node number of the other system
   %P      point number of the other system
   %D      domain name of the other system (if available)
   %n      complete address of the other system
   %I      name of <GlobalInbound>
   %O      name of <GlobalOutbound>
   %S      name of Sysop of other system
   %d      direction: 1 if inbound call, -1 if outbound call
   %x      this TrxID string
   %X      remote TrxID string
   %m      line number of this system


Example:   FaxInCommand="Fax %C"


See also:     @{"FaxString" Link "MS Fax FaxString"}

@EndNode

@Node "MS Fax FaxInPri" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Fax/FaxInPri"
@Next "MS Fax FaxInStack"
@Prev "MS Fax FaxInCommand"
@Toc  "MS Fax"

Name:      FaxInPri=<pri>

   Set the priority of the <FaxInCommand> command.


Example:   FaxInPri=2

@EndNode

@Node "MS Fax FaxInStack" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Fax/FaxInStack"
@Next "MS Fax FaxOutCommand"
@Prev "MS Fax FaxInPri"
@Toc  "MS Fax"

Name:      FaxInStack=<dimensione>

   Set the stack size for <FaxInCommand> command.


Example:   FaxInStack=8000

@EndNode

@Node "MS Fax FaxOutCommand" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Fax/FaxOutCommand"
@Next "MS Fax FaxOutPri"
@Prev "MS Fax FaxInStack"
@Toc  "MS Fax"

Name:      FaxOutCommand=<comando>

   During  a  call, when GMS mailer detects a fax connection, it will spawn
this external program.

   There may be embedded %-commands:

   %a      aka of the remote system (one aka per %a)
   %A      all akas of the remote system (space separated)
   %b      baudrate (between computer and modem)
   %B      baudrate (of the actual connection)
   %C      full CONNECT message from the modem
   %s      serial device name
   %u      serial device unit number
   %f      serial device flags
   %r      unique random number (timestamp)
   %l      name of logfile
   %L      name of log callerID
   %Z      zone number of the other system     
   %N      net number of the other system
   %F      fido node number of the other system
   %P      point number of the other system
   %D      domain name of the other system (if available)
   %n      complete address of the other system
   %I      name of <GlobalInbound>
   %O      name of <GlobalOutbound>
   %S      name of Sysop of other system
   %d      direction: 1 if inbound call, -1 if outbound call
   %x      this TrxID string
   %X      remote TrxID string
   %m      line number of this system


Example:   FaxOutCommand="Fax %C"


See also:     @{"FaxString" Link "MS Fax FaxString"}

@EndNode

@Node "MS Fax FaxOutPri" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Fax/FaxOutPri"
@Next "MS Fax FaxOutStack"
@Prev "MS Fax FaxOutCommand"
@Toc  "MS Fax"

Name:      FaxOutPri=<pri>

   Set the priority of the <FaxOutCommand> command.


Example:   FaxOutPri=0

@EndNode

@Node "MS Fax FaxOutStack" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Fax/FaxOutStack"
@Next "MS Fax FaxString"
@Prev "MS Fax FaxOutCommand"
@Toc  "MS Fax"

Name:      FaxOutStack=<dimensione>

   Set the stack size for <FaxOutCommand> command.


Example:   FaxOutStack=8000

@EndNode

@Node "MS Fax FaxString" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Fax/FaxString"
@Prev "MS Fax FaxOutStack"
@Toc  "MS Fax"

Name:      FaxString=<string>

   Is  the  string  that  GMS  mailer  will search in the CONNECT string to
determine if it is a Fax connection.


Example:   FaxString=FAX


See also:     @{"FaxInCommand" Link "MS Fax FaxInCommand"}, @{"FaxOutCommand" Link "MS Fax FaxOutCommand"}

@EndNode

@Node "MS Hs" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Handshakes"
@Next "MS Log"
@Prev "MS Fax"
@Toc  "CFG MailerSettings"

   @{b}Handshake options@{ub}


   How to set up all handshake supported in GMS mailer.

 @{" FTS-1      " Link "MS Hs FTS-1"}
 @{" YooHoo     " Link "MS Hs YooHoo"}
 @{" Emsi       " Link "MS Hs Emsi"}
 @{" Emsi-II    " Link "MS Hs Emsi-II"}

 @{" EmsiDomain " Link "MS Hs EmsiDomain"}

@EndNode

@Node "MS Hs FTS-1" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Handshakes/FTS-1"
@Next "MS Hs YooHoo"
@Toc  "MS Hs"

Name:      FTS-1=<boolean>

   Enable/disable FTS-1 handshake.

   The oldest protocol for a FidoNet session. Needed for Fidonet compliancy.


Example:   FTS-1=ON

@EndNode

@Node "MS Hs YooHoo" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Handshakes/YooHoo"
@Next "MS Hs Emsi"
@Prev "MS Hs FTS-1"
@Toc  "MS Hs"

Name:      YooHoo=<boolean>

   Enable/disable YooHoo handshake. Only capable of handling a single AKA.
YooHoo is otherwise known as WaZoo.


Example:   YooHoo=ON

@EndNode

@Node "MS Hs Emsi" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Handshakes/Emsi"
@Next "MS Hs Emsi-II"
@Prev "MS Hs YooHoo"
@Toc  "MS Hs"

Name:      Emsi=<boolean>

   Enable/disable Emsi handshake.

   This is the newest handshake protocol for the FidoNet network. EMSI is
capable of sharing all your AKAs with the other mailer where as FTS-1 and
YooHoo are only capable of communicating a single AKA.


Example:   Emsi=ON

@EndNode

@Node "MS Hs Emsi-II" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Handshakes/Emsi-II"
@Next "MS Hs EmsiDomain"
@Prev "MS Hs Emsi"
@Toc  "MS Hs"

Name:      Emsi-II=<boolean>

   Enable/disable Emsi-II handshake.

   This  is the newest handshake protocol for the FidoNet network.  EMSI-II
is  an  extension  of  EMSI handshake and give him other new options as the
Fall-back to YooHoo and FTS-1 and many others.


Example:   Emsi-II=ON

@EndNode

@Node "MS Hs EmsiDomain" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Handshakes/EmsiDomain"
@Prev "MS Hs Emsi"
@Toc  "MS Hs"

Name:      EmsiDomain=<boolean>

   Enable/disable 5D addresses in Emsi handshake.


Example:   EmsiDomain=ON

@EndNode

@Node "MS Log" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Log"
@Next "MS Modem"
@Prev "MS Hs"
@Toc  "CFG MailerSettings"

   @{b}Log options@{ub}


   How to set up all logs features...

 @{" CIDMode         " Link "MS Log CIDMode"}
 @{" CIDLogMode      " Link "MS Log CIDLogMode"}
 @{" LogFile         " Link "MS Log LogFile"}
 @{" LogCallerID     " Link "MS Log LogCallerID"}
 @{" LocalizeLog     " Link "MS Log LocalizeLog"}
 @{" LocalizeLogDate " Link "MS Log LocalizeLogDate"}
 @{" MaxLogLines     " Link "MS Log MaxLogLines"}
 @{" MaxLogSecs      " Link "MS Log MaxLogSecs"}

 @{" LogDebugger     " Link "MS Log LogDebugger"}
 @{" LogInformation  " Link "MS Log LogInformation"}
 @{" LogLink         " Link "MS Log LogLink"}
 @{" LogModem        " Link "MS Log LogModem"}
 @{" LogOutside      " Link "MS Log LogOutside"}
 @{" LogScheduler    " Link "MS Log LogScheduler"}
 @{" LogSecurity     " Link "MS Log LogSecurity"}
 @{" LogSession      " Link "MS Log LogSession"}
 @{" LogSystem       " Link "MS Log LogSystem"}
 @{" LogTransfer     " Link "MS Log LogTransfer"}
 @{" LogUser         " Link "MS Log LogUser"}

@EndNode

@Node "MS Log CIDMode" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Log/CIDMode"
@Next "MS Log CIDLogMode"
@Toc  "MS Log"

Name:      CIDMode=<Ring|Connect>

   Set the mode that defines how GMS should grab the CID.

 - Ring:     Grab the CID between the first and the second ring.
 - Connect:  Grab the CID between the ring anf the connect string.


Example:   CIDMode=Ring

@EndNode

@Node "MS Log CIDLogMode" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Log/CIDLogMode"
@Next "MS Log LogCallerID"
@Prev "MS Log CIDMode"
@Toc  "MS Log"

Name:      CIDLogMode=<Log|Date+Log|MainLog>

   Set the mode of how write the log file.

 - Log:       Use the LogCallerID to write the log.
 - Date+Log:  As above but insert also the date.
 - MainLog:   Insert the CallerID informations into the LogFile file.


Example:   CIDLogMode=MainLog

@EndNode

@Node "MS Log LogFile" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Log/LogFile"
@Next "MS Log LogCallerID"
@Toc  "MS Log"

Name:      LogFile=<filename>

   Set the name of log file.


Example:   LogFile=Mail:GMS_mailer.Log

@EndNode

@Node "MS Log LogCallerID" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Log/LogCallerID"
@Next "MS Log LocalizeLog"
@Prev "MS Log LogFile"
@Toc  "MS Log"

Name:      LogCallerID=<filename>

   Set the name of CallerID log file.


Example:   LogCallerID=Mail:GMS_mailer.IDLog

@EndNode

@Node "MS Log LocalizeLog" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Log/LocalizeLog"
@Next "MS Log LocalizeLogDate"
@Prev "MS Log LogCallerID"
@Toc  "MS Log"

Name:      LocalizeLog=<boolean>

   Enable/disable log localization.


Example:   LocalizeLog=YES

@EndNode

@Node "MS Log LocalizeLogDate" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Log/LocalizeLogDate"
@Next "MS Log MaxLogLines"
@Prev "MS Log LocalizeLog"
@Toc  "MS Log"

Name:      LocalizeLogDate=<boolean>

   Enable/disable date log localization.


Example:   LocalizeLogDate=YES

@EndNode

@Node "MS Log MaxLogLines" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Log/MaxLogLines"
@Next "MS Log MaxLogSecs"
@Prev "MS Log LocalizeLogDate"
@Toc  "MS Log"

Name:      MaxLogLines=<lines>

   This  allows  you  to  specify  the  number  of  log-lines  that will be
buffered,  i.e.   after so many lines have been written to the logfile, the
file  will  be flushed (closed and reopened, in order to force all the data
to disk).

   Is you set this to 0, the logfile will be flushed after every line.


Example:   MaxLogLines=10

@EndNode

@Node "MS Log MaxLogSecs" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Log/MaxLogSecs"
@Next "MS Log LogDebugger"
@Prev "MS Log MaxLogLines"
@Toc  "MS Log"

Name:      MaxLogSecs=<seconds>

   This  specifies  the number of seconds that may expire before GMS mailer
will flush the logfile.

   Is you set this to 0, the logfile will be flushed after every line.


Example:   MaxLogSecs=10

@EndNode

@Node "MS Log LogDebugger" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Log/LogDebugger"
@Next "MS Log LogInformation"
@Prev "MS Log MaxLogSecs"
@Toc  "MS Log"

Name:      LogDebugger=<level>

Level=<Silent|Terse|Discreet|Verbose|Talkative|Excessive|Annoying|Monologue>

   Set the value for <LogDebugger> keyword.

Level        Text
-----        ----
Terse        "No EMSI figerprint"
Verbose      "EMSI-Send: %s"
Verbose      "EMSI-Rec: %s"
Annoying     "EMSI-Send: %s"  (EMSI_DAT)
Annoying     "EMSI-Rec: %s"   (EMSI_DAT)
Verbose      "YooHoo-Send: %s"
Verbose      "YooHoo-Rec: %s"
Monologue    "Modem returned: "%s""
Silent       "Could not open Serial: "%s""
Silent       "Could not open LogFile: "%s""
Silent       "Could not open Nodelist"
Silent       "Could not open traplist.library v5"
Discreet     "Serial device owned..."
Discreet     "Serial device released..."
Terse        "Reloading configs..."
Silent       "Could not own Serial: "%s""
Discreet     "Reloaded standard config"
Discreet     "Reloaded config line %ld"
Silent       "Invalid addresses in EMSI..."


Example:   LogDebugger=Monologue

@EndNode

@Node "MS Log LogInformation" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Log/LogInformation"
@Next "MS Log LogLink"
@Prev "MS Log LogDebugger"
@Toc  "MS Log"

Name:      LogInformation=<level>

Level=<Silent|Terse|Discreet|Verbose|Talkative|Excessive|Annoying|Monologue>

   Set the value for <LogInformation> keyword.

Level        Text
-----        ----
Silent       " Name: %s (%s)"
Discreet     "  AKA: %s"
Terse        "SysOp: %s"
Discreet     "Place: %s (%s)"
Excessive    "Flags: %s"
Talking      "Using: %s"
Annoying     "Offer: %s"
Excessive    "Hold: %s"
Excessive    "Keep: %s"
Verbose      "TrxID: %s/%s"
Verbose      "TrxID: %s"


Example:   LogInformation=Monologue

@EndNode

@Node "MS Log LogLink" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Log/LogLink"
@Next "MS Log LogModem"
@Prev "MS Log LogInformation"
@Toc  "MS Log"

Name:      LogLink=<level>

Level=<Silent|Terse|Discreet|Verbose|Talkative|Excessive|Annoying|Monologue>

   Set the value for <LogLink> keyword.

Level        Text
-----        ----
Excessive    "Connection made at %ld Bd"
Verbose      "Line is busy"
Verbose      "Modem reported error"
Verbose      "Voice answer"
Verbose      "No connection"
Verbose      "No dial tone"
Silent       "Carrier lost"
Discreet     "Baudrate too low"


Example:   LogLink=Terse

@EndNode

@Node "MS Log LogModem" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Log/LogModem"
@Next "MS Log LogOutside"
@Prev "MS Log LogLink"
@Toc  "MS Log"

Name:      LogModem=<level>

Level=<Silent|Terse|Discreet|Verbose|Talkative|Excessive|Annoying|Monologue>

   Set the value for <LogModem> keyword.

Level        Text
-----        ----
Silent       "Modem not ready"
Talkative    "Initializing modem"
Silent       "Initializing modem failed"
Verbose      "Hanging up modem"
Annoying     "Already hung up"
Silent       "Could not hang up"
Excessive    "Hang up completed"
Talkative    "Modem dialing"
Talkative    "Modem answering"
Terse        "%s" (CONNECT, NO CARRIER, BUSY, VOICE, NO DIALTONE, ...)
Discreet     "%s" (RINGING)


Example:   LogModem=Silent

@EndNode

@Node "MS Log LogOutside" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Log/LogOutside"
@Next "MS Log LogScheduler"
@Prev "MS Log LogModem"
@Toc  "cfgLog

Name:      LogOutside=<level>

Level=<Silent|Terse|Discreet|Verbose|Talkative|Excessive|Annoying|Monologue>

   Set the value for <LogOutside> keyword.

Level        Text
-----        ----
Discreet     "Spawning %s: "%s""
Silent       "Can't spawn %s (Error %ld)"
Talkative    "%s returned (%ld)"
Verbose      "Executing %s: "%s""
Silent       "Can't execute %s (Error %ld)"
Silent       "Can't open BBS input/output file"


Example:   LogOutside=Silent

@EndNode

@Node "MS Log LogScheduler" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Log/LogScheduler"
@Next "MS Log LogSecurity"
@Prev "MS Log LogOutside"
@Toc  "MS Log"

Name:      LogScheduler=<level>

Level=<Silent|Terse|Discreet|Verbose|Talkative|Excessive|Annoying|Monologue>

   Set the value for <LogScheduler> keyword.

Level        Text
-----        ----
Silent       "GMS mailer v%s opened"
Silent       "GMS mailer v%s closed"
Verbose      "Waiting for call"
Discreet     "Incoming call detected"
Terse        "Calling %s"
Talkative    "Calling %s (%s)"
Terse        "Phone %s"


Example:   LogScheduler=Monologue

@EndNode

@Node "MS Log LogSecurity" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Log/LogSecurity"
@Next "MS Log LogSession"
@Prev "MS Log LogScheduler"
@Toc  "MS Log"

Name:      LogSecurity=<level>

Level=<Silent|Terse|Discreet|Verbose|Talkative|Excessive|Annoying|Monologue>

   Set the value for <LogSecurity> keyword.

Level        Text
-----        ----
Silent       "Password-protected session"
Verbose      "Expected %s and got %s"
Silent       "Bad password on other end (remote: "%s")"
Silent       "Bad password (remote: "%s")"
Terse        "Bad password for AKA %s (remote: "%s")"
Excessive    "Unlisted system"
Silent       "%s exceeds account limits"
Silent       "Can't find node %s"
Silent       "Unknown password"
Silent       "%s (%s) is undialable"


Example:   LogSecurity=Silent

@EndNode

@Node "MS Log LogSession" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Log/LogSession"
@Next "MS Log LogSystem"
@Prev "MS Log LogSecurity"
@Toc  "MS Log"

Name:      LogSession=<level>

Level=<Silent|Terse|Discreet|Verbose|Talkative|Excessive|Annoying|Monologue>

   Set the value for <LogSession> keyword.

Level        Text
-----        ----
Terse        "Session connect time %ld:%02ld:%02ld"
Verbose      "Session aborted"
Silent       "Remote system does not respond"
Excessive    "Begin of session"
Discreet     "Protocol: %s/%s"
Excessive    "Call successful"
Excessive    "Call failed"
Excessive    "End of send"
Silent       "No common protocol available"
Silent       "Can't find any call keywords in your configuration file"
Silent       "Remote system does not acknowledge handshake"
Terse        "Session connect time %ld:%02ld:%02ld, cost %ld.%02ld"
Terse        "Session connect time %ld:%02ld:%02ld, sent %ld%s, recv %ld%s"
Terse        "Session connect time %ld:%02ld:%02ld, cost %ld.%02ld, sent %ld%s, recv %ld%s"
Terse        "Session connect time %ld:%02ld:%02ld, cps %ld, errs %ld"
Terse        "Session connect time %ld:%02ld:%02ld, cost %ld.%02ld, cps %ld, errs %ld"
Terse        "Session connect time %ld:%02ld:%02ld, sent %ld%s, recv %ld%s, cps %ld, errs %ld"
Terse        "Session connect time %ld:%02ld:%02ld, cost %ld.%02ld, sent %ld%s, recv %ld%s, cps %ld, errs %ld"


Example:   LogSession=Terse

@EndNode

@Node "MS Log LogSystem" "GMS_mailer.guide/MailerSettings/Log/LogSystem"
@Next "MS Log LogTransfer"
@Prev "MS Log LogSession"
@Toc  "MS Log"

Name:      LogSystem=<level>

Level=<Silent|Terse|Discreet|Verbose|Talkative|Excessive|Annoying|Monologue>

   Set the value for <LogSystem> keyword.

Level        Text
-----        ----
Silent       "Disk I/O error"
Terse        "User break"
Silent       "Not implemented"
Silent       "Out of memory"
Silent       "Can't access GlobalInbound directory"
Silent       "Can't access GlobalOutbound directory"
Silent       "Can't open "%s""
Terse        "File "%s" is in use"
Annoying     "Flagging file as sent"
Excessive    "Deleting file"
Excessive    "Truncating file"
Annoying     "Deleting %s"
Silent       "Internal error"
Silent       "Value of DropBBSSecs too low, corrected to 10"
Silent       "DOS error: %ld (0x%lx)"
Verbose      "RetryRead: %ld successful"
Silent       "RetryRead: %ld failed"
Verbose      "RetryWrite: %ld successful"
Silent       "RetryWrite: %ld failed"
Discreet     "Timer "%s" expired"
Discreet     "Can't truncate "%s""
Silent       "No addresses in EMSI handshake"


